November was like a years worth of hugs at once. So grateful for these friends I call family. 

1) Breakers Supper club is a devine experience and being able to share it with Deneé and Marq was icing on the cake.

2) Deneé broke a bat at the rage cage & the crew and I lost our MINDS at the new Blue Ivy documentary.

3) Jelly is everything. 

4) Deneé and I burning it all away under the full moon.

5) for Saum’s bday we escape room hopped. THREE ROOMS (one of which was jank as fuck) all completed WAY under the allotted time… the last one… with the two jail cells and separate groups. EPIC.

6) friends don’t let friends hold on to the rage… they get suited up in a protective gear and break 20 plates, a printer, a computer , keyboard… i don’t even know honestly. This was top ten most cathartic experiences of my life. And sharing it with you was exactly what i needed. I love you Deneé. 💋 it’s December and the blister is STILL healing. Metaphors on metaphors.

7) would it be a 2023 post on my page if I didn’t give you a lil mirror pic Papi

8) I tell this story like I’m her mother. I saw Ali PICK UP THE GUITAR and say “I think I’m gonna learn how to play this” and now she’s a friggin rockstar. Like WHAT?? I’m endlessly proud of you friend. 

9) a lil more supper club because I love yall and Marq was getting the GOOD GOOD pics that night. Yall see that joy?! 

10) Tank and the Bangas with the boys. Sharing this night with you two was perfect. Healing. Lovely. Hilarious. That fucking Taylor swift club afterwards sksksksksk. More of Deon’te and Ephraim in 2024. Please. Also if yall don’t know tank and the bangas get in because the writing/music is incredible.

This is from my shoot with @emilcohen 

Transcript of what I said below :) 

This picture and the pictures that follow were taken by @emilcohen exactly one year ago today and I barely recognize myself.

What a fucking year it’s been, yall.

When I say I barely recognize myself I mean im starring at myself in the mirror right now and looking at this picture and the boy in the picture is an incredibly distant memory. That boy was going through it. Life had just started beating him up in a way he didn’t know was possible. Yall,2023 was complete and utter shit. I’m just being mother fucking honest. I will look back at this year and just scoff. But the guy in the pic? I look at him and though I barely recognize him…I’m proud. Because the guy I’m looking at in the mirror now? He’s strong. Powerful. So beautiful. He’s grown so damn much. And he is ready. 

Look, I know life does what it does. There is no control. There’s belief in whatever you believe in and running head first at it. But at the end of the day life is truly how you perceive it. And I’m glad that I’ve finally gotten to the place where my perception can find the positive again . I thought I had lost that ability. I actually started to think it was a RIDICULOUS ability to have. But it’s back now. I can find the joy. And I have. And nothing can take that away from me again.

Nakie Baby New Year.
2023 I fell in love with my body. And now- in 2024 you can too 😉 !!!

Nah but in all seriousness, this shoot with @michaelyoungphotography who I have been friends with for over 10 years now, was one of my favorite things to come out of 2023. We spent an entire day talking, exchanging ideas and being VULNERABLE. This photo is a physical representation of that night, the year that is now GONE (hallelujah 🙌🏽) and a moment of stillness in the storm. I LOVE THIS PHOTO and though it is a little scary to put it on the internet, it is me. It is me at my barest. In front of all of you. Letting each one of yall know that 2024 is about to be gagged by what I do. That’s not just an affirmation it’s a PROMISE. Yall ain’t seen nothing yet. 

Happy New Year to all of you.
